    "description": "Sigagents is an R-based visualization package, designed to enable the users with limited programming experience to produce statistical plots of continuous genomic data. It consists of several statistical visualizations that provide insights regarding the behavior of a group of signals in large regions – such as a chromosome or the whole genome – as well as visualizing them around a specific point or short region.",
